/*

VECTORS :- Array ki replacement hai vector. 
Vector ek dynamic array hai jisme hum elements ko add aur remove kar sakte hain bina kisi size ke restriction ke. 
Vector ka size automatically badhta hai jab hum usme elements add karte hain.

array ka size fixed hota hai jab hum usko declare karte hain, lekin vector ka size dynamic hota hai.
Vector ke andar elements contiguous memory locations par store hote hain, isliye vector ka access time O(1) hota hai, matlab constant time hota hai.
Vector ke andar elements ko add karne ke liye push_back() function ka use karte hain, aur elements ko remove karne ke liye pop_back() function ka use karte hain.
Vector ke andar elements ko access karne ke liye [] operator ka use karte hain, aur size() function ka use karke vector ke size ko pata kar sakte hain.

*/